<h2 class="section-heading">Guiding Principles</h2>
<p>At Moi High School Kabarak, every decision we make and every student we shape is anchored in three guiding lights: a clear Vision, a purposeful Mission, and unwavering Core Values. Together they define who we are, what we do, and why we do it.</p>

<div class="mvv-grid">
  <div class="mvv-card">
    <span class="mvv-icon"></span>
    <h3>Our Vision</h3>
    <p>To be a <strong>Christian School of Choice</strong>  the institution that families, communities, and the nation trust to nurture the next generation.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="mvv-card featured">
    <span class="mvv-icon"></span>
    <h3>Our Mission</h3>
    <p>To provide holistic educational services in a learner-centered, co-educational Christian set-up, guided by the values of commitment, fairness, and integrity  remaining accountable to the maxim of excellence in all our undertakings.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="mvv-card">
    <span class="mvv-icon"></span>
    <h3>Core Values</h3>
    <p>The principles we live by, daily, on the playground and in the classroom:</p>
    <div class="values-row">
      <span class="value-pill">Commitment</span>
      <span class="value-pill">Fairness</span>
      <span class="value-pill">Integrity</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="section-heading">Living Our Values</h2>
<p><strong>Commitment</strong> means showing up  for our students, for our standards, for our faith. From the chalkboard to the chapel, we don't do anything halfway.</p>
<p><strong>Fairness</strong> guides how we discipline, how we grade, how we choose leaders, and how we treat every member of the MHSK family  regardless of background or status.</p>
<p><strong>Integrity</strong> is the silent partner in every transaction at Kabarak. It's what our students carry out into the world long after they leave our gates.</p>

<div class="commitment-quote">
  "In fulfilling our mission, we remain accountable to the maxim of <strong>excellence in all our undertakings</strong>."
</div>
